{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I am a marine toxicologist,"},{"time":2000,"text":"and I've been very, very concerned about the Gulf,"},{"time":5000,"text":"particularly about the massive applications"},{"time":8000,"text":"of the toxic dispersants,"},{"time":10000,"text":"the Corexits."},{"time":12000,"text":"I've been working on ocean pollution"},{"time":14000,"text":"for quite a long time --"},{"time":16000,"text":"the impacts on marine life and particularly the impacts"},{"time":19000,"text":"on marine mammals."},{"time":21000,"text":"As it turns out, marine mammals"},{"time":23000,"text":"are at the top of this food chain"},{"time":25000,"text":"that we're pouring millions of tons"},{"time":28000,"text":"of toxic substances into"},{"time":30000,"text":"every year."},{"time":32000,"text":"And they are showing the signs of this."},{"time":35000,"text":"I'm sorry to have a sad slide like this,"},{"time":37000,"text":"but not everything is all that happy,"},{"time":40000,"text":"especially in my work."},{"time":44000,"text":"They are loaded"},{"time":46000,"text":"with toxic chemicals in their body,"},{"time":48000,"text":"hundreds of compounds,"},{"time":50000,"text":"all kinds of compounds -- it's staggering."},{"time":52000,"text":"And they're dying off rather regularly,"},{"time":54000,"text":"tens of thousands around the world."},{"time":57000,"text":"It's predicted they may go extinct --"},{"time":59000,"text":"about a third of them --"},{"time":61000,"text":"within about 30 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63000,"text":"So my project is along the Northwest Atlantic."},{"time":66000,"text":"It's called Seals as Sentinels."},{"time":68000,"text":"We're tracking pollution"},{"time":70000,"text":"at the top of the food web, in marine mammals and fish."},{"time":73000,"text":"It's a region-wide,"},{"time":75000,"text":"eco-toxicological investigation."},{"time":78000,"text":"We're looking at a lot of compounds,"},{"time":80000,"text":"but recently been quite interested in"},{"time":82000,"text":"the flame retardants, the brominated flame retardants"},{"time":85000,"text":"that are in many, many things"},{"time":87000,"text":"that we use in our everyday life,"},{"time":89000,"text":"from the cushions in the chairs"},{"time":91000,"text":"we're all sitting on"},{"time":93000,"text":"to the plastic casings of our computers,"},{"time":96000,"text":"our television sets and so on."},{"time":98000,"text":"So we are tracking"},{"time":100000,"text":"how do these things get from"},{"time":102000,"text":"the products into the ocean,"},{"time":104000,"text":"which is the final sink for them."},{"time":106000,"text":"And there's quite a complicated pathway for that"},{"time":109000,"text":"because, as these products age,"},{"time":111000,"text":"they get concentrated in dust,"},{"time":113000,"text":"and then they also get thrown out, so they go to the landfills."},{"time":116000,"text":"They wind up in waste water treatment plants."},{"time":119000,"text":"As you all know, we throw out billions"},{"time":121000,"text":"of computers and TVs every year."},{"time":123000,"text":"And those go to e-waste dumps."},{"time":125000,"text":"And all that gets into surface waters,"},{"time":127000,"text":"eventually reaching the ocean, the final sink."},{"time":129000,"text":"So, in our study,"},{"time":131000,"text":"we did find quite high levels, as we expected,"},{"time":134000,"text":"of these flame retardants in the harbor seals' bodies."},{"time":137000,"text":"And we reported this."},{"time":139000,"text":"It led to a ban of this neuro-toxic flame retardant"},{"time":142000,"text":"called Deca in Maine, where I am based,"},{"time":145000,"text":"and also then a phase-out,"},{"time":147000,"text":"U.S.-wide, at the end of last year."},{"time":150000,"text":"But we said, well, on the bright side,"},{"time":152000,"text":"our harbor seals at least will not be"},{"time":154000,"text":"bursting into flame anytime soon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":158000,"text":"So then I got really curious,"},{"time":160000,"text":"myself, as a toxicologist,"},{"time":162000,"text":"and I donated some blood to my lab"},{"time":164000,"text":"and said, \"Okay, let's do it.\""},{"time":166000,"text":"Well, we detected 113 different compounds"},{"time":169000,"text":"in my blood."},{"time":171000,"text":"And I must say, if any of you would have this done,"},{"time":174000,"text":"you'd probably find a similar profile,"},{"time":176000,"text":"or cocktail, as they call it."},{"time":178000,"text":"But I was the recipient"},{"time":181000,"text":"of a lot of flame retardant material for some reason."},{"time":184000,"text":"And just to point out the levels --"},{"time":187000,"text":"Americans have 10 to 40 times higher"},{"time":190000,"text":"levels of these compounds in our bodies"},{"time":192000,"text":"than the Europeans."},{"time":194000,"text":"Why? Because we are flame-retarding everything,"},{"time":197000,"text":"and we have weak regulations"},{"time":199000,"text":"for toxic chemicals."},{"time":201000,"text":"But lo and behold, I'm one of the high-end individuals."},{"time":204000,"text":"Lucky me."},{"time":206000,"text":"But then I thought,"},{"time":208000,"text":"well, in case of a fire, I might be the last one to ignite."}]},{"cues":[{"time":211000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":214000,"text":"So anyway, here's the problem --"},{"time":216000,"text":"and it is a problem that we're looking at in the Gulf today --"},{"time":219000,"text":"we're not regulating chemicals in this country properly."},{"time":222000,"text":"We're hardly regulating them at all."},{"time":225000,"text":"And we're letting industry run the show."},{"time":227000,"text":"And Jackie Savitz spoke this morning"},{"time":229000,"text":"about Big Oil"},{"time":231000,"text":"and the propaganda"},{"time":233000,"text":"and how we're all brainwashed"},{"time":236000,"text":"with their, you know, lies and so forth."},{"time":239000,"text":"Well, Big Chemical"},{"time":241000,"text":"is what we're dealing with here."},{"time":243000,"text":"And they're allowed to keep trade secrets,"},{"time":245000,"text":"so they don't even give the ingredients out."},{"time":248000,"text":"Plus they don't give health and safety data,"},{"time":250000,"text":"so, consequently, they cannot be regulated"},{"time":253000,"text":"before they go to market."},{"time":256000,"text":"So it's a case of innocent until proven guilty."},{"time":259000,"text":"The burden of proof is not on the producer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262000,"text":"So I then was invited to go"},{"time":264000,"text":"to the Gulf in May."},{"time":266000,"text":"I went down there on"},{"time":268000,"text":"a preliminary investigation"},{"time":270000,"text":"to look into dispersants"},{"time":272000,"text":"and how they're going into the water column and so forth."},{"time":274000,"text":"And I was told that I was"},{"time":276000,"text":"the only toxicologist to date"},{"time":279000,"text":"who was dumb enough to get into the water,"},{"time":281000,"text":"but I did."},{"time":283000,"text":"And we dove in the slick"},{"time":285000,"text":"without even HazMat gear."},{"time":288000,"text":"And I did get sick."},{"time":291000,"text":"I got a ferocious sore throat two days later."},{"time":294000,"text":"I felt like my throat was on fire."},{"time":297000,"text":"But it did pass."},{"time":299000,"text":"And what I did see in the water as we went down,"},{"time":302000,"text":"what really shocked me -- and it's haunted me ever since --"},{"time":305000,"text":"because I could see the droplets of oil dispersing."},{"time":308000,"text":"And as you go down, they're catching all kinds of plankton,"},{"time":311000,"text":"bumping into,"},{"time":313000,"text":"you know, little wisps of life"},{"time":315000,"text":"that are the food for the planktivores,"},{"time":318000,"text":"the herring kind of fish."},{"time":321000,"text":"And you could just see the web of death"},{"time":323000,"text":"as you go down in the water column."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325000,"text":"Well, you know, we got into this"},{"time":327000,"text":"in the beginning"},{"time":329000,"text":"as a trade-off, they say,"},{"time":331000,"text":"between the wetlands versus the ocean depth."},{"time":334000,"text":"And I didn't agree with that"},{"time":336000,"text":"decision at the time; I still don't."},{"time":338000,"text":"The decision was to protect the marshes."},{"time":341000,"text":"When the oil gets into the marshes, you can't get it out."},{"time":344000,"text":"And as you know, there's been a very weak response,"},{"time":346000,"text":"up until recently,"},{"time":348000,"text":"to actually collect the oil."},{"time":350000,"text":"It's gotten much more aggressive."},{"time":352000,"text":"This is an Exxon slide showing what happens,"},{"time":355000,"text":"the scenario and the trade-off."},{"time":357000,"text":"So this shows oil on the surface."},{"time":359000,"text":"You can see it getting up into the mangrove,"},{"time":362000,"text":"but it is not harming the corals"},{"time":365000,"text":"or the sea grass, right."},{"time":367000,"text":"So here we have the other scenario."},{"time":370000,"text":"If you disperse, the sea grass and the corals"},{"time":372000,"text":"are getting hit pretty hard,"},{"time":374000,"text":"but you're saving the mangrove."},{"time":376000,"text":"So this, to me, is like going to the eye doctor, okay?"},{"time":379000,"text":"Is it better with one or two?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":382000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":384000,"text":"The problem is that we have"},{"time":386000,"text":"released so darn much of this stuff,"},{"time":388000,"text":"we're climbing up to two million gallons"},{"time":391000,"text":"very quickly."},{"time":394000,"text":"And then there's the problem of the plumes."},{"time":397000,"text":"What plumes?"},{"time":399000,"text":"It turns out there are plumes."},{"time":402000,"text":"Independent researchers found that."},{"time":404000,"text":"And then there's the looming,"},{"time":407000,"text":"messy problem of human health,"},{"time":409000,"text":"reported human health effects."},{"time":411000,"text":"And actually, one of our federal officials"},{"time":413000,"text":"said that it was probably heat stress. So ..."},{"time":418000,"text":"Having been in that water"},{"time":420000,"text":"just for the short time I was there,"},{"time":422000,"text":"I can tell you, it is not heat stress."},{"time":424000,"text":"There are volumes of volatile"},{"time":426000,"text":"petroleum fumes coming off that water,"},{"time":429000,"text":"plus the Corexit,"},{"time":431000,"text":"which has solvent in it."},{"time":433000,"text":"So it is not at all rational."}]},{"cues":[{"time":436000,"text":"So what do we have? The BP show is going on."},{"time":439000,"text":"Our officials complained about Corexit,"},{"time":442000,"text":"which is the most toxic"},{"time":445000,"text":"line of dispersants."},{"time":447000,"text":"But heck, they're still using it,"},{"time":449000,"text":"and they used the most toxic one, the 9527,"},{"time":452000,"text":"until they ran out of supplies."},{"time":455000,"text":"Now they're on 9500."},{"time":457000,"text":"9527 had 2-butoxyethanol in it"},{"time":460000,"text":"that causes internal bleeding."},{"time":463000,"text":"We know that from the Exxon Valdez spill, by the way."},{"time":466000,"text":"So what we're doing, we're putting compounds"},{"time":469000,"text":"with petroleum solvents onto a petroleum spill."},{"time":472000,"text":"Does this make sense?"},{"time":474000,"text":"So this is the way it works."},{"time":476000,"text":"And I want to show you this cute little thing that happens here."},{"time":479000,"text":"It's a micelle."},{"time":481000,"text":"Micelles form around the oil."},{"time":484000,"text":"And what happens first"},{"time":486000,"text":"is the solvents break into the oil,"},{"time":488000,"text":"the lipid membrane,"},{"time":490000,"text":"they let the surfactants in there."},{"time":492000,"text":"The surfactants -- which are like things"},{"time":494000,"text":"we use on fast food wrappers --"},{"time":496000,"text":"they grab around the droplets of oil,"},{"time":498000,"text":"and they make little, tiny droplets"},{"time":500000,"text":"with nice, little"},{"time":502000,"text":"surfactant edges to them."},{"time":504000,"text":"The thing to remember about the micelles --"},{"time":507000,"text":"these little floating"},{"time":509000,"text":"globules of toxin --"},{"time":511000,"text":"is they are there to deliver."},{"time":513000,"text":"They're like the FedEx guys."},{"time":515000,"text":"And if you're a fish,"},{"time":517000,"text":"and you haven't gotten your glob in the morning,"},{"time":519000,"text":"you're going to get it in the afternoon,"},{"time":521000,"text":"because they've got your number."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523000,"text":"So from a toxicology perspective,"},{"time":526000,"text":"this is really awful"},{"time":528000,"text":"because Corexit and the dispersed oil"},{"time":531000,"text":"are much more toxic together"},{"time":533000,"text":"than either alone."},{"time":535000,"text":"And usually the exposure"},{"time":537000,"text":"is a combined exposure."},{"time":539000,"text":"The dispersants -- as I was saying --"},{"time":542000,"text":"their job is to break down"},{"time":544000,"text":"the lipid membrane."},{"time":546000,"text":"The solvents in them do that very efficiently."},{"time":549000,"text":"So they break down"},{"time":551000,"text":"lipid membranes in our body,"},{"time":553000,"text":"starting with cells of the skin,"},{"time":555000,"text":"the cells of organs."},{"time":557000,"text":"So it actually hastens"},{"time":559000,"text":"oil getting into the body"},{"time":561000,"text":"easily and readily."},{"time":563000,"text":"Oil contains hundreds of hydrocarbon compounds"},{"time":566000,"text":"and other compounds"},{"time":568000,"text":"that are toxic to every organ in the body."},{"time":571000,"text":"And so with the dispersants combined,"},{"time":573000,"text":"you have this very synergistic"},{"time":575000,"text":"combined toxicity."},{"time":578000,"text":"Corexit also contains petroleum solvents"},{"time":580000,"text":"and many other toxic compounds."},{"time":582000,"text":"And I'm part of a chat group,"},{"time":584000,"text":"which is a national group"},{"time":587000,"text":"of toxicologists and chemists"},{"time":590000,"text":"that are, you know, basically"},{"time":592000,"text":"turning cartwheels trying to figure out what's in this stuff,"},{"time":595000,"text":"and what is it doing and what are the interactions"},{"time":598000,"text":"of these chemicals, most of which we don't know,"},{"time":601000,"text":"and what are their byproducts,"},{"time":603000,"text":"which are usually more toxic than the parent compound."},{"time":606000,"text":"So we did find that Corexit 9500"},{"time":608000,"text":"contains heavy metals, arsenic and chromium --"},{"time":611000,"text":"arsenic at high enough levels"},{"time":614000,"text":"to have cancer-causing effects."}]},{"cues":[{"time":618000,"text":"So this is what we have to look at,"},{"time":621000,"text":"these, you know, ridiculous safety data sheets,"},{"time":624000,"text":"which have nothing on them much."},{"time":627000,"text":"And now they were forced to release the ultimate list"},{"time":630000,"text":"of everything that's in Corexit."},{"time":633000,"text":"And guess what,"},{"time":635000,"text":"tons of stuff is missing."},{"time":637000,"text":"Derivatives, derivatives, these are whole big groups"},{"time":640000,"text":"of many, many compounds, these sorbitans."},{"time":643000,"text":"And then you get down to the petroleum distillates,"},{"time":645000,"text":"which are the solvents,"},{"time":647000,"text":"hundreds of them."},{"time":649000,"text":"They are not identified. And why?"},{"time":652000,"text":"Trade secrets again."},{"time":654000,"text":"BP's running the show,"},{"time":656000,"text":"and the Nalco company, this is all they have to do."},{"time":659000,"text":"So far these ingredients have not been released,"},{"time":662000,"text":"and toxicologists are actually going nuts"},{"time":665000,"text":"because we cannot predict with certainty"},{"time":668000,"text":"what the interactions"},{"time":670000,"text":"and toxic results are going to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":672000,"text":"But we do have quite a lot at risk"},{"time":674000,"text":"down there, as we all know,"},{"time":676000,"text":"the 33 wildlife refuges,"},{"time":679000,"text":"so much wildlife"},{"time":681000,"text":"and fish and diversity."},{"time":683000,"text":"So we know from previous spills."},{"time":685000,"text":"And then part of this is just"},{"time":687000,"text":"part of my bad dreams."},{"time":689000,"text":"And I appreciate being able"},{"time":691000,"text":"to vent some of my"},{"time":693000,"text":"anguish upon you."},{"time":695000,"text":"What we do know is that the corals are going to get hit hard."},{"time":699000,"text":"And this is a study that was done"},{"time":701000,"text":"on the Australian coast,"},{"time":703000,"text":"the coast of Tasmania."},{"time":706000,"text":"Corals are, you know, the home to"},{"time":708000,"text":"about a quarter of all marine species."},{"time":710000,"text":"And with the Corexit"},{"time":713000,"text":"and the oil,"},{"time":715000,"text":"there's zero percent fertilization."},{"time":718000,"text":"With oil alone, there's 98 percent fertilization."},{"time":721000,"text":"So they're a very sensitive species"},{"time":723000,"text":"to this combo."}]},{"cues":[{"time":725000,"text":"Here's another group."},{"time":727000,"text":"I could see myself easily in the water column."},{"time":730000,"text":"The plankton and the plankton eaters,"},{"time":732000,"text":"you know, these are the little herring fish"},{"time":734000,"text":"that go through the water column with their mouths open,"},{"time":737000,"text":"feeding indiscriminately"},{"time":739000,"text":"and just lapping up"},{"time":741000,"text":"this brown pudding of toxic stuff."},{"time":745000,"text":"And we do know from other studies"},{"time":747000,"text":"that this is a highly toxic mixture."},{"time":749000,"text":"See the oil and Corexit is causing death"},{"time":752000,"text":"at a much, much lower dose"},{"time":755000,"text":"than oil alone."},{"time":757000,"text":"That's probably as far as what we do know"},{"time":759000,"text":"about toxic effects."},{"time":761000,"text":"But my bad dreams go like this."},{"time":764000,"text":"The piscivorous fish,"},{"time":766000,"text":"the cobia, grouper, amberjacks, those big fish,"},{"time":769000,"text":"also the tuna and sharks,"},{"time":771000,"text":"are going to hit by this."},{"time":773000,"text":"And the gills are quite sensitive."},{"time":775000,"text":"The respiratory system is very sensitive."},{"time":777000,"text":"Think about it with"},{"time":779000,"text":"the Corexit hitting the membranes,"},{"time":782000,"text":"and it will clog up the gills,"},{"time":785000,"text":"and then these animals are going to be"},{"time":787000,"text":"getting something like what you call"},{"time":789000,"text":"chemical pneumonia,"},{"time":791000,"text":"trying to aspirate the compounds."},{"time":794000,"text":"It also will cause internal bleeding"},{"time":796000,"text":"upon ingestion."},{"time":798000,"text":"I'm very worried about the air-breathing mammals because I study them,"},{"time":801000,"text":"but also, the way their going to be exposed"},{"time":803000,"text":"is every time they come to the surface to take a breath,"},{"time":806000,"text":"they're going to inhale these volatile fumes."},{"time":809000,"text":"And what does happen with that eventually"},{"time":811000,"text":"is pneumonia sets in"},{"time":814000,"text":"and liver, kidney, brain damage."},{"time":817000,"text":"The Corexit"},{"time":819000,"text":"is transporting the oil"},{"time":821000,"text":"into every membrane"},{"time":823000,"text":"and every system of the body."},{"time":825000,"text":"And you're having"},{"time":827000,"text":"a lot of different unpleasant effects,"},{"time":829000,"text":"but burns to the eyes and mouth,"},{"time":832000,"text":"skin ulcers, lesions."},{"time":834000,"text":"And I think, personally,"},{"time":836000,"text":"that we have not begun to see"},{"time":838000,"text":"the impacts of this spill"},{"time":840000,"text":"on the wildlife of the Gulf."}]},{"cues":[{"time":842000,"text":"We started hypothesizing:"},{"time":844000,"text":"what do we know?"},{"time":846000,"text":"what do with think would be a trophic cascade?"},{"time":848000,"text":"which means that somebody gets wiped out,"},{"time":850000,"text":"and then everything above"},{"time":852000,"text":"that's eating those guys will crash."},{"time":854000,"text":"So our thought was --"},{"time":857000,"text":"this is a simple thinking process, but ..."},{"time":859000,"text":"obviously the plankton, the planktivores,"},{"time":862000,"text":"and that's about as far as we got."},{"time":864000,"text":"And then it turns out we're not very good at figuring this stuff out."},{"time":867000,"text":"This is what the Exxon Valdez scientists thought would happen,"},{"time":870000,"text":"this trophic cascade"},{"time":872000,"text":"where you lose the kelp and the herring"},{"time":874000,"text":"and other fishes and going up."},{"time":876000,"text":"They thought that eventually the killer whale"},{"time":878000,"text":"would be at the top of this cascade."},{"time":880000,"text":"And then here's what really happened,"},{"time":882000,"text":"much more complicated, much more specific."},{"time":885000,"text":"Actually the kelp"},{"time":887000,"text":"and the barnacles that attach to the rock"},{"time":890000,"text":"were decimated by the combination"},{"time":892000,"text":"of Corexit and the oil."},{"time":896000,"text":"They were replaced by invasive species,"},{"time":899000,"text":"which had less holding power to the rock."},{"time":902000,"text":"Storms came along."},{"time":904000,"text":"They ripped out of the rock."},{"time":906000,"text":"And this was the entire food web for the sea ducks."},{"time":909000,"text":"And as you know, we lost about 300,000 sea ducks"},{"time":912000,"text":"from the Exxon Valdez spill,"},{"time":914000,"text":"and they haven't come back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":917000,"text":"So we are launching"},{"time":919000,"text":"an independent study."},{"time":921000,"text":"And by independent, I do not mean alone;"},{"time":924000,"text":"I mean independent in the sense"},{"time":926000,"text":"of not tied to"},{"time":929000,"text":"the kind of crime-scene secrecy"},{"time":931000,"text":"that's going on in the Gulf now."},{"time":933000,"text":"But we are actually going to be assessing toxic impacts,"},{"time":936000,"text":"but we need lots and lots of partners"},{"time":938000,"text":"to do this intelligently."},{"time":940000,"text":"We have some of the partners lined up."},{"time":942000,"text":"And Dave Gallo signed on."},{"time":944000,"text":"Sylvia's in here."},{"time":947000,"text":"And we hope that some of you will help us."},{"time":950000,"text":"My question to you is: why shouldn't we know?"},{"time":952000,"text":"Don't we have the right to know?"},{"time":954000,"text":"Surely we have the right to learn"},{"time":957000,"text":"what loss we are going through in the Gulf."},{"time":960000,"text":"And my wish would be --"},{"time":963000,"text":"for the gulf prize -- would be"},{"time":965000,"text":"that we have the truth."},{"time":968000,"text":"Whatever it is, please let us have the truth."},{"time":971000,"text":"And to get there,"},{"time":973000,"text":"we need to do the assessment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":976000,"text":"So I appreciate being here. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":978000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}